deck: The clerk who found Evan Pepper's finger.
description:
Origin

Working at McBerty's Burgers, Daniel discovered a human finger among one of it's burgers. Given to Tony Chu, the cibopath, Chu found out that the finger belonged to Evan Pepper. Chu pressured Daniel into revealing that they had some black market chicken in the back of the fast food restaurant.
name: Daniel Cornblum

deck: Health inspector for the state of New York. His finger was chopped off after he discovered a warehouse full of illegal chicken meat.
description:
Origin

Evan Pepper is a health inspector for the state of New York, with territories concentrated around Williamsburg, Brooklyn. When he discovered a warehouse full of illegal chicken meat, he got grabbed by the henchmen and his finger got chopped off as a warning. But he never made it out of the warehouse, because he was killed by Mason Savoy to silence Evan Pepper.

The finger ended up in a burger, where it was discovered by Daniel Cornblum and given to Tony Chu, the FDA cibopath, to eat and solve the murder.
name: Evan Pepper

deck: Former editor-in-chief of Amelia Mintz. He was once taken hostage by the terrorist group E.G.G.
description:
Storyline

Herb is the editorial chief for the Mercury Sun. Herb was held hostage by a gang of individuals, called E.G.G,. wanting to hijack his paper to print propaganda against the FDA and the U.S Government.

Amelia Mintz was working for him until she quit after the problem with E.G.G. Later, Herb agreed to hire Amelia Mintz back to write as long as she reported on real news as opposed to her previous food critic articles.
name: Herb Urlacher

deck: Nomi Haupai was the governor of the island Yamapalu.
description:
Storyline

As the governor of the only place in the world, the Pacific island Yamapalu, where the gallsaberry grows, Haupai actively promotes the fruit, which tastes like chicken. This is very important in a world where chickens are outlawed after the avian flu killed many people.

When his gallsaberry empire imploded, he committed suicide.
name: Governor Haupai
